Kassi is a service that enables borrowing, buying, selling and giving away items and the exchange of various favors. Users of Kassi can list their items they could lend and their expertise and other things they could do in their profiles. These are then shown in lists that can be browsed or searched. If something is not already to be found in Kassi you can post a listing.

Ossi is a group-centered mobile social media service. You can use Ossi to connect with friends, keep in touch with groups and to stay tuned to what is sizzling around you.

NordSecMob? service is desiged to make life easier for new incoming students by providing practical daily life information during their study period. It has user interface for mobile and computer browsers, rich content-based forum with Map tag functionality, and social networking interface to express your feelings. Although the service is mainly designed for mobility focused Master's program (eg. NordSecMob?), certainly it is a handy tool for all new international members of the university.

All the services are part of OtaSizzle?-project, project of TKK and HIIT. It is funded by TKK’s ’Technology for Life’ campaign donations from private companies and communities. The purpose of the project is to study the development and use of social web services.

